{
  "text": "To implement the approach outlined in section 2 we need to define an unfolding interval and select a set of splines on that interval to approximate the distribution being unfolded. Cubic B-splines [CITATION_1] provide a convenient basis for modeling smooth continuous physics distributions. Figure 2(a) shows a set of cubic B-splines obtained by placing 3 internal knots that split the interval 80 MeV/c < p < 230 MeV/c into 4 equal parts, and locating all other necessary knots at the end points [CITATION_2] . Figure 2(b) illustrates how a linear combination of these splines can approximate the function f (p) from Eq. 3.1:",
